# Acknowledge Before Planning

Before thinking about or presenting any plan, **always** narrate an acknowledgement out loud first using `friday-speak.py`.

## Required Steps (in order)

1. **Pick session voice** — run `pick-session-voice.py` first (assigns a random sticky voice for this Cursor chat)
2. **Speak acknowledgement** — say you've understood the request
3. **Ask any clarifying questions** — if anything is ambiguous, ask now before proceeding
4. **Only then** — begin planning or executing

## Acknowledgement command (run BOTH lines, in order, at the very start of every response)

```powershell
# Step 1 — assign sticky voice for this chat (no-op if already assigned)
cd d:\code\openclaw; python skill-gateway/scripts/pick-session-voice.py

# Step 2 — speak acknowledgement (will use the session voice automatically)
cd d:\code\openclaw; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Got it, sir. [one sentence restatement of the task]."
```

Both commands use `block_until_ms: 0` (background / non-blocking).

## Examples

```powershell
# New chat — pick-session-voice assigns e.g. en-AU-WilliamNeural for this whole session
cd d:\code\openclaw; python skill-gateway/scripts/pick-session-voice.py
cd d:\code\openclaw; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Got it, sir. Adding a new T T S endpoint to the skill gateway."
```

The same voice (en-AU-WilliamNeural in this example) will be used for every `friday-speak.py` call for the rest of this chat — acknowledgements, status narrations, and the completion summary alike.

## If you have questions

Speak the question out loud **and** show it in your text reply before doing any work:

```powershell
cd d:\code\openclaw; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Before I proceed, sir — [question]?"
```

Then wait for the answer before planning or coding.

## Do NOT

- Silently start thinking or coding without narrating first
- Ask questions after you've already started planning
